<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.6.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.6.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.6.0</Version>
    <!-- v0.6.6.0 — pure numeric versioning per "Option 3" decision after v0.6.5.3a.
         Letter-suffix versions (0.6.5.3a) cause toolchain friction with release.ps1
         (which tags from numeric Version) and the github-actions repo.json bot
         (which expects numeric semver). Letter suffixes deprecated; iterate by
         bumping the numeric Build component. The InformationalVersion property and
         IncludeSourceRevisionInInformationalVersion flag have been removed from this
         csproj. UI/MainWindow.cs ResolveVersion() retains the InformationalVersion-
         preferring code path — dormant infrastructure for future use if we ever
         need pre-release tags or build metadata, but not actively populated. -->
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics — BiS planner, gear inventory reader, materia advisor for FFXIV. v0.6.6.0 is the next attempt at BUG-001 (the Materia Advisor header ghost text). Prior swings: v0.6.5.2 (pre-pad, wrong), v0.6.5.3 (collision-node param, wrong), v0.6.5.3a (H1 removed bidirectional sibling-link patch — changed the bug pattern but didn't eliminate it). v0.6.6.0 tests hypothesis H6: the cloned label cell inherits the original ILVL row's text geometry, and our "── Materia Advisor ──" label (with em-dashes) overflows the inherited cell width, bleeding into the number cell's render zone. The intervention this time is one targeted change in StatusPanelInjector.cs: shorten the advisor header label from "── Materia Advisor ──" to "Materia Advisor" — no dashes. If H6 is correct, ghost goes away or shrinks dramatically. Plus a bonus consistency fix: Plugin.cs BuildGoblinInfoString() now reads from UI.MainWindow.ResolveVersion() instead of its own duplicate version-formatter, so /ttinfo and the in-game header pill always agree on what version is loaded. Pure numeric versioning going forward (Option 3): no more letter-suffix versions; iterate by bumping the numeric Build. Core and Web at v0.6.6.0 lockstep (version-only). Mobile site work slides to v0.6.6 (it was tentatively scoped for v0.6.6.0 before BUG-001 turned into a multi-version saga). See BUG_HUNT_AND_ROADMAP.md for the experiment plan; if H6 is confirmed, v0.6.5.5 ships the proper Width-fix (H6-B); if H6 is wrong, v0.6.5.5 tries the next hypothesis.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!--
    v0.6.3: ProjectReference to the shared GearGoblin.Core library.
    Path assumes the standard sibling-of-grandparent layout:

        D:\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\        (Core, this reference's target)
        D:\GearGoblin-v0.1\GearGoblin\                  (this project)
        D:\TonberryTactics-workspace\TonberryTactics\   (web, mirrors this same reference)

    If Core lives somewhere else on your machine, update the path to
    point at your local clone. The web's csproj uses the same relative
    pattern so both halves resolve to the same library on disk.

    Plugin's existing MeldOptimizer (already job-aware via JobProfile)
    continues to function unchanged in v0.6.3 — Core integration on
    the plugin side is incremental, tracked for v0.7.x alongside the
    CPR-replacement work. Today's ProjectReference exists so future
    migrations are mechanical rather than gated on adding a dependency.
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\..\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\GearGoblin.Core.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>

